{"body": "The only difference I see between `is_a?` and `class.<` is related to comparable class itself (i.e `A.new.is_a?(A) == true`, but `A < A == false`). But as I have mentioned above, ActiveRecord::Base can not be instantiated, so its direct instance can't be passed in this method.\r\n\r\nThe duck-typing is common in ruby, and if developer can implement some class, whose instances behave like  ActiveRecord::Base instances, why not?\r\n\r\nI can write some tests, if you point me on untested behavior.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/23016883", "created_at": "2013-08-21T13:30:43Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/11945#issuecomment-23016883", "updated_at": "2013-08-21T13:30:43Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 11945, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mik-die/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mik-die/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mik-die/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mik-die", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mik-die/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/Mik-die", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mik-die/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/7d116b912a4fc7986b40d5d0d0d811d6?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fa587d6b5be4a306d5b73620593d05627.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mik-die/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mik-die/received_events", "gravatar_id": "7d116b912a4fc7986b40d5d0d0d811d6", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mik-die/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "Mik-die", "type": "User", "id": 426230, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mik-die/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5237cff8bd3543c151007c1b"}, "id": 23016883, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/11945"}
